decommissionDam(address).details: Decommissions the DAM and schedules a withdrawal to the specified receiver. 			All remaining funds in the DAM will be sent to the receiver.

params.receiver: The address to receive the remaining funds in the DAM.

deposit(uint256).details: Deposits the specified amount into the DAM, applying it to the ongoing round.

params.amount: The amount of funds to deposit.

depositWithPermit(uint256,uint256,uint8,.details: deposits the specified amount into the dam, applying it to the ongoing round via permit function.

params.amount: the amount of funds to deposit.
params.deadline: the deadline timestamp that the permit is valid.

endRound(bytes,uint8,bytes32,bytes32).details: Ends the current round, verifies data integrity, and processes withdrawal if any.

params.data: Data required to finalize the round. 				It includes the following: 				- List of addresses to receive grants 				- List of grant proportions

getTotalIncentive().details: returns the interest generated in the current round.

returns._0: totalincentive the total amount of incentive that goes to the projects.
returns._1: reinvestmentamount the amount of interest reinvested into the next round.

operateDam(uint256,uint256,uint16,uint16.details: Starts the DAM operation with specified parameters.

params.amount: The amount of funds that will be the source of yield.
params.autoStreamRatio: The percentage of yield allocated to automatic grant distribution.
params.period: The duration of each round in seconds.
params.reinvestmentRatio: The percentage of yield reinvested back into the treasury.

operateDamWithPermit(uint256,uint256,uin.details: Starts the DAM operation with specified parameters via permit function. see: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-2612 and https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-713

params.amount: The amount of funds that will be the source of yield.
params.autoStreamRatio: The percentage of yield allocated to automatic grant distribution.
params.deadline: The deadline timestamp that the permit is valid.
params.period: The duration of each round in seconds.
